inn1.comm: and Watto has driven the first delivery of the day for four, a superb square-drive, full and wide, gets on a knee and cracks it past point
he is going for everything here, short and wide, angling away, and he throws the kitchen sink at it and misses, all fielders safe too
gets it closer to him, slightly fuller too, Watson shoulders arms
a touch fuller, just outside off, angling away, Watson pushes forward and shoulders arms again
Aamer gets even fuller, in Watson's zone, and he unleashes another big drive, in front of cover this time, same result
goes back to back of a length, pitched just outside off, lets it go
a length delivery outside off, Watson thinks of a drive, but lets it go undisturbed
squares Shaun Marsh first ball, perfect delivery for the left-hander, just back of a length, pitching middle and leg, angling towards the slips, the thick edge gets him off the mark
decent pace, 140ks, just outside off, short of a length, and Watson lets it go
pulled to long-on, this is not short enough, but Watson gets under it and up and over mid-on, and despite overnight rain, the outfield is fast
good comeback, juags back in from back of a length, 143ks, drops his wrists in a defensive shot
the pull shot again, it's not short enough, but he pulls well, along the ground this time, through midwicket
fuller delivery, aimed at top of off, Watson can't do much with it, and defends
on target, not too short, at the off stump, Marsh defends
misses out on that leg-side half-volley, a touch early into the attempted whip
a slight leading edge as Marsh looks to turn this off his pads, rolls along to cover
gets his line back to around off again, on a length, 145ks, pushed to mid-off
clever shot, gets some room to free his arms, guides it past the two slips, keeps it all along the ground, Gul's dive from third man is in vain. Good use of Aamer's pace
nearly a yorker, around the off line, and played down to mid-on
short and wide, cut away past point, thank you, come again
fuller this time, outside off, Watson gets his back pad across and lets it go
this shot has paid a lot of bills for Watto, too short again, and he is in the position to pull early, and takes it from outside off, up and over midwicket
slightly fuller, and Watson judges it well and chooses to not go after it
it's slightly shorter and wider, and enough for Watson to cut it, but it goes through the gully region and he gets a single to third man
gets the length right for Marsh, just back of a length, angling across him, and Marsh defends it back to the bowler
the first streaky shot from Watson, a big drive with an open face from wide outside off, gets enough bat on it to clear the cover ring
pulls the length back a bit, looks to run it down to third man, can't beat backward point
in the Watson driving zone, he goes for it, no half measures, and even though he has skied it down the ground, he has got enough bat on it to disappoint mid-off running back
short, gets width to cut, and cut he does, wide of third man, gets two
that's a good aggressive bouncer, 146ks, aimed at the throat, Watson ducks
another big drive outside off, again he gets enough to clear the cover ring, this over has been a bit of a tease for the Pakistan fielders inside the ring on the off side
just back of a length, not much room, forced to defend this to cover
gets the length right again, just outside off, Watson makes a brave leave, but this doesn't nip back
this is a touch shorter, and Watson runs it down to third man, Aamer does well to keep them down to one, gets an applause from the crowd behind him
angling across him, slapped away powerfully, gets a single down to third man
looks to guide it to third man, but it's too close to do so, misses both the inside edge and the off stump
no room again, pushed to midwicket
looks to drive from wide outside off, gets a thick edge to third man
misses out, this is short around his hip, he pulls, can't beat the short fine leg fielder
angled across him, and he slashes and misses
looks to run it off the face of the bat down to third man, but this lone slip is wide, around where third slip would be, and it goes one bounce to Younis there
good sharp bouncer, 143ks, rising as Watson sways put of the way, rising even more by the time it reaches Kamran who jumps high and gets a hand to it, but can't prevent a bye
full delivery, around off, defended back to the bowler
just back of a length, outside off, pushed to cover
he pulls a good-length delivery, gets it to deep square leg, all along the ground
full delivery, around middle, angling away, dead-batted back
play and a miss, outside off, Marsh getting slightly edgy
good delivery, cuts him in two, Marsh pre-meditates a chop third man, but there is no room to do so, lucky not to get the inside edge
strays onto the pads, worked away with soft hands, and comes back for two before the deep square leg fielder can come in
good start, a dip in the pace, 133ks, but right on the target, neither driveable nor cuttable, and just outside off
on target again, not much room, Watson covers the off stump, and lets it go through to Kamran
good running, he just drops it at his feet, and comes through for one before the gully fielder, Umar Akmal, can come around
length ball, around the middle stump, cramping him, pushed to midwicket
worked away off the pads, gets a single
What. A. Shot. He has pulled a full delivery here, bends at the knee, gets under this length delivery, and launches it into the stand at midwicket
angled across him, and he runs it down to third man, and hands over the strike to Watson
short, wide, smack, gets under it, and crashes it over point
nips back in this time, has to drop his wrists in the defensive shot
pulled away again, but this is two bounce to deep square leg, he will prefer to go over midwicket because of the fielder stationed there
slightly outside off, shapes to cut, but decides against the shot
Marsh gets into action, short, gentle pace, rocks back, and pulls it through midwicket. Double barrel now
goes for the paddle over short fine, but misses, extra bounce too
slower ball, comes out a fulltoss, he hits it over midwicket, not cleanly, but enough to clear the infield, what a 50 for Watson, the crowd is going crazy
short, rapid this time, beats him in the pull shot
yorker, digs it out to midwicket, straight to the fielder, still he comes for the single, and has to pull in the full-length dive to beat Younis's throw - he would have been in had Younis hit
on target, just outside off, defended to cover
gets width this time, runs it down to third man for a single
nicely flighted first ball, no turn, pushed back to the bowler
works a fulltoss off the pads to deep midwicket
driven right into the ground, one bounce to cover
overspinning quicker delivery, almost squeezes through
full outside off, another one-bounce drive to cover
lovely shot, waits and waits and then runs it past short third man, Rana puts in a good chase
hint of swing, in towards Watson, pushed down to mid-off
too short, and Watson's pull goes to the right of deep square leg, another superb shot
superb running, plays it down to third man with soft hands, and before Umar Akmal runs back, slides and fields and throws, they are back for two
goes for the big booming drive outside off, gets a thick edge towards third man
pushed off the front foot towards mid-off
good push-drive outside off, can't beat cover
flat ball, he gets back and across and defends
fuller ball, punched down the ground
tossed up on middle and leg and he presses forward
full toss outside off stump, pushed down to long-off
fuller ball, some spin, presses forward and keeps it out
shorter ball, slides on, he makes room and dabs it wide of slip
tossed up from around the stumps, gets some drift and turn, Marsh pushes and gets a controlled edge that flies into the open spaces
flat and short, some spin, he defends off the back foot, Marsh wants one but Watson says no
shot! Watson gets back in a flash and rides the bounce, creating a wee bit of room to pounce and cut that nice and late behind point
shuffles and knocks the ball to the on side for his highest ODI score in Australia
slowly tossed up, some turn, Marsh pushes off the front foot to cover
slider, comes forward and pushes it back
flipper on middle and leg, Marsh uses the wrists and drives but Afridi dives across to his left side and does well
gets back and dabs this one but the fielder cuts it off
opens the face and dabs a slider past backward point
fuller ball, some turn, pressed off the front foot to cover
slower one, angles past, defended off the front foot
spins back, he makes room and runs it to backward point
runs is down to short third, can't beat the fielder
flat delivery, cuts, Butt puts in the dive at backward point
flighted around off, no turn, defended back to the bowler
pushes this one through, into the pads, pushed to midiwcket
gets one short, cuts, but can't beat backward point
flat, quick delivery, just outside off, played towards point
slightly slower, presses forward and defends
smart bowling, slower through the air, Watson goes for the big shot to the leg side, misses, is saved the lbw by the bounce
flatter now, outside off, defended
short and wide, and he pulls into the vacant on-side circle, gets a single to deep midwicket
plays this one with soft hands towards point and Watson rushes through for a single
flighted outside off, driven inside-out, gets a single to wide long-off
pushed through, into the pads, 95ks, can't get it past square leg
topspinner, just outside off, punched to sweeper-cover
is beaten on the premeditated sweep
looks to run it down to third man, the ball doesn't turn, inside follows him and cramps him up
another premeditated sweep, connects this time, gets a single
googly, sharp pace too, pushed to point
again the get-away sweep, gets the single to bring up the hundred
looks to cut, but it is too full, the bottom edge goes one bounce to slip
almost squeezes through with the quicker one, but Watson's bat comes down in time

so the pressure put in by the spinners has worked, throws this one up gently after having pinned him on the back foot, Watson goes for the flick-sweep, not the all-out powerful shot, just the flick-sweep, but he has times it too well, and it carries to deep square leg where Malik takes a smart catch
drives this down the ground, gets a single to long-on
cuts it from in front of the stumps, can't get it past short third
presses forward and defends
superb sweet shot, takes it from in front of the stumps, and bisects fine leg and deep square leg
powerful drive, down the ground, gets a single
slightly back of a length, turning in, goes deep into the crease and defends
turning into the pads, wants a single, but it's gone straight to square leg
flat delivery, pushed back to the bowler
another quick delivery, cut uppishly, but right between backward point and short third man
fuller, slower, worked away to long-on
full delivery outside off, left alone
back closer to the stumps, 87ks, slower to the new batsman
this is pushed through, 101ks, pushes it to cover
short delivery, worked around the corner, gets a single
looks to work it to leg, the ball doesn't turn, the leading edge goes back to the bowler
another straighter delivery, played back to the bowler
this is a regulation offbreak, thrown up outside off, Ponting defends, the bowler can't find any bat-pad gap
shorter, punched from outside off, gets a single
goes for the late cut, straight to Gul at short third
short and wide, pushed to sweeper-cover for one
overpitched on the pads, flicked to midwicket

Afridi gets two! looks for the chip over the on side, the bat face turns early, the leading edge carries all the way to long-on, and Afridi is in his Flintoffesque celebration, arms aloft, letting the mates surround him and hug him
short, worked away to cover for one
pads away a delivery wide outside off
flatter, on the stumps, defended down the ground
looks to work it to square leg, ends up playing to midwicket
soft hands here, gets a sharp single to short fine
hits on the run, rather runs on the hit, comes forward, works it away, and starts running in the same motion, gets a couple to wide of deep midwicket
dances down the track, can't get it past square leg this time
flatter, 101ks, stays in the crease and pushes it back to the bowler
jumps out of the crease again, pushes it down to long-off for one
short, outside off, pushes it down to long-off for one
short and wide, ripe for the cut, but squeezes under his bat
this time he gets the cut shot going, gets a single to sweeper-cover
short and wide again, and cut away square of sweeper-cover, gets a couple
again the googly, again he almost gets it through him, the bat comes down just in time
shorter, slower, gives him time, to work it to midwicket for a single
steps out to Ajmal again, gets to the pitch of it and takes a single to long-on
stays in the crease and pushes it down to long-on
this is shorter, goes deep in the crease, but the punch can't get past Yousuf at extra cover
pout of his crease again, single down the ground again
cut from in front of the stumps, gets a single to third man
flat and full, 102ks, keeps Clarke in the crease, pushed back to the bowler
angled across Ponting, he drops it at his feet and comes through for one
plays outside the line of the ball, pitched outside the leg stump, but doesn't go quite as far with the angle, but he gets two leg-byes for it
runs this one down to third man, and gets a single
fuller delivery, Ponting looking onside, but it's not there for the shot, and he defends it back to the bowler
slower ball, 133ks, beats him outside off
he sees short ball, he pulls short ball, good-looking short too, swivelling with it, can't beat the deep fielder, though
nice offbreak, works it away for a single to short fine
steps out of the crease again, can't beat midwicket with the push
short, sits up to be pulled, but can;t beat deep square leg with the shot
comes onto the front foot, can't get it past midwicket
jumps out of the crease, and plays a chip shot to wide long-on
Younis is sharp at midwicket, the third ball this over that has been worked away to him for no run
comes down the pitch, and is beaten outside off, Ponting looking edgy
lunges forward, wants a single to cover, but Malik is sharp there
full ball, on the pads, nicely played wide of square leg, gets a couple
it was on the cards, looks to loft him over mid-on, is half a second early into the shot, and ends up lobbing it straight to Yousuf at mid-on. Aamer is ecstatic, Ponting is furious
pushes forward and defends just outside off
good bouncer, straight over the stumps, throat-high, 138ks, White ducks
short, fla, hurrying on him, pushed to midwicket
dances down the wicket, turns this one into a fulltoss, gets a single to long-off
comes forward and flicks it towards the non-striker, Malik makes a good diving save
another push down the ground, but Younis gets around from midwicket and keeps him on strike
this time he successfully pushes him down to long-on
short outside off, punched away, but straight to extra cover
lovely delivery to start off with, outside off, back of a length, moves away a touch, beats the tentative poke
more on the stumps, worked away to fine leg
back of a length, just outside off, pushed to cover
short, kicks up, beats Clarke with the bounce, but they come through for a leg-bye
good bouncer, no room, head-high, White is too late into the pull shot
beats him with the inward movement, and extra bounce too, looks to work a length delivery from in front of stumps, but is hit in the thigh pad
flighted around off, driven back to the bowler
steps out again, and pushes it down to long-on
flat delivery, into the pads, worked away for a single
he comes out of the crease again, the offbreak takes the inside half of the bat, to square leg
this time he manges to push the toppie down to long-off
short, punched down the ground for a single
offcutter, cramping him up for room, can't succeed at his attempt to run it down to third man
pulled away off the front foot, first boundary in 12 overs, this one sits up to be hit, and he gets it clear of midwicket
another shortish delivery, stands tall and punches it to the off side, can't get it past extra cover
looks to run it down to third man again, and is cramped up by another offcutter
pulls, sharper bouncer, top-edged, is rushed into it, one bounce to fine leg, no-ball anyway
slower ball, picks his spot, and plays the pick-up shot over the on side, makes the four look easy
steps out of the crease, runs this shortish delivery down to third man
full, on the pads, helped away for a single
flat delivery into the pads, gets a single to square leg
fuller, and again can't get it past midwicket, Younis has been superb there
short outside off, guides it down to third man
flat again, not giving it much air, punched down to long-on
lovely inside-out shot, always a treat to watch, jumps out of the crease, makes room, and chips it over extra cover
shortish, outside off, presses forward, and defends
short, 140ks, White slashes, is beaten by the extra bounce, Kamran goes for the shout right away, but there is no edge, in fact White is beaten for the pace
another short ball, the bottom hand comes off the cut shot, gets a single to third man

goes for the inside-out, over-the-extra-cover shot, but the length is not there, it' too short for the shot, and he chips it straight to Afridi at extra cover. Clarke walks back, Pakistan form a huddle
shoulders arms to a ball outside off, five men saving single
gets a thick edge wide of slip, gets off the mark
nice floater, angling across him, played towards short third
flighted outside off, defended
looks for the drive into the covers, cramped for room, gets a single down to long-off
short, outside off, pushed down to long-off
short and wide, cut away, Rana makes a good diving save at deep point
tucks him up with a quick straight delivery, another dot
wide down the leg side
short on the pads, gets a single to square leg
shot! low fulltoss, timed really well, wide of mid-off, Yousuf gets a hand onto it and saves the boundary
looks to work it around the corner, gets an inside edge onto the pads, and gets another single
short and wide, cut away for a single
length ball, across him, can't get it past point
another outside edge from Hussey, will get a single down to third man
full and straight, pushed down the ground, gets a single
looks for big powerful cut, no room again, gets the bottom edge into the ground and through to the keeper
full delivery, hit to wide long-off for one
flighted gently, outside leg, taken on the full, swept away, gets two
flatter delivery, fast, tucks him up, played back to the bowler
Afridi's quota comes to an end with a terrible misfield from Yousuf at midwicket, yet his figures read 10-0-35-2
worked away off the pads, soft hands too, into the gap, and he rushes back for two
and again, helped away off the pads, gets just a single this time, though
soft hands, drops it down towards short third and comes through for one
full, on the pads, misses out, can't beat midwicket
full, outside off this time, pushed down the ground for one
beauty, superb delivery, back of a length, outside off, holds its line as opposed to coming in with angle, and beats a poke from White
sharp offbreak, around off, defended towards point
second dot, pushed back to the right of the bowler who does well
lap shot, premeditated, but connects well, gets a single
another sharp offbreak, follows White as he makes room, cramps him up completely
fired into the pads, played back to the bowler
again no room, sharp pace, around off, and defended back, superb over, just a single off
beats him with an offcutter, perfect delivery too, pitches middle and seams away
this time he gets behind the line and opens the face of the bat
length ball, driven powerfully, gets just a single to long-off
and he beats the outside edge again, Hussey steps out this time, and again he is beaten by the away movement, this is not just the angle, but movement upon pitching
this is an easier delivery on the pads, but can't beat midwicket
length ball pushed down the ground for one, another superb over, just three off
short delivery, timed well, but straight to extra cover
this is too short, gives him enough time to go back and pull it between long-on and deep midwicket, nice shot
punched away from outside off, gets a single to sweeper-cover
looks for the inside-out shot, makes room, Ajmal follows him, he can't get under it, gets just a single
pushed down to long-off for one
again he follows him up with a sharp offbreak, and White - who has backed away quite a distance - is still cramped up for room
pushed to left of mid-off for a single
yorker, he digs it down to long-on for a single
pushed to extra-cover, Hussey rushes through and dives in for a single
superb shot, walks across the stumps, gets a length delivery, plays the pick-up shot towards midwicket, there's a man getting under it, but he is in the 15th row in the stands
goes for the same shot, Rana bowls in the slower one, and he is through the shot ages below the ball arrives
another superb shot, flat, bounces about two feet inside the boundary, goes across and over midwicket again, lovely timing
short and wide, gets a thick edge, beats a diving Gul at short third
backs away, Ajmal follows him, can't beat extra cover, can't get any power into it
this time bowls a doosra as opposed to following him, too far away from him, toe edge
cut away, can't beat Afridi at point
fuller, pushed down the ground for one
dropped, how costly will this be? makes room and hits it back to Ajmal, who has to merely stretch to get to it, but lets it through
angling across him, gets a single down to third man

Malik takes a second good catch today, Hussey looks for the pull, the ball isn't short enough, the top edge lobs between short fine and deep square leg, Malik is the man running in and finishes a safe catch
angled across him, gets a single to cover
short ball, tucks him up, worked away off the hips
full delivery, pushed down the ground, just a single
slower delivery, 129ks, angling across him, he drops and runs
length ball, gives him space to free his arm, crashes it wide of long-off, Umar Akmal is alert and fires in a superb throw to keep them to two
fuller, almost a yorker, can't get under it, gets a single to mid-on
whips it across the line, can't get it wide enough of midwicket
slower ball, wide outside off, gets a single to point
swiped across the line, gets a single to midwicket
length ball, hits down the ground, wide enough of long-on to come back for two
looks to make room, Aamer doesn't let him, follows him, played back to the bowler
nice bouncer, White is late into the shot, 142ks, is hit in the shoulder
another superb delivery at the death, straight yorker this time, inside edge gets him a single
good old-fashioned slog, gets the length to get under, and clears midwicket with it
low fulltoss, hit straight to mid-on
good shot, gooood shot, deliberately drags it from in front of middle to wide of mid-on, finds the gap between mid-on and midwicket
drives away from the body, gets it through the gap between cover and point, gets a couple
Malik has been superb in the outfield today, Haddin swipes this slower delivery across the line, Malik dashes from long-on, prevents four, comes back and throws fast and flat
lucky four here, makes room to go inside-out, gets a thick edge, beats short third
follows him with a yorker, no room, can't get under it either
superb hit to get to a 50, looks to make room, Gul goes wide, White follows him and gets enough bat to clear the cover ring
low fulltoss, slogs, mis-hits, but into the gap it the on side, gets three, 16 off the over
lovely yorker, White is making room, and he follows his toe, superb delivery
thigh-high fulltoss, throws his all at it, gets a top edge, Rana runs from deep square leg and almost completes what would have been an incredible catch
sharp bouncer, lovely delivery, no room, and White is late into the pull again, lobbing it top Yousuf at midwicket. Mark Nicholas on air says, "He [Aamer] is quite something, if he really is 17."
slogs after making room, mis-hits, gets just a single, it is bowled at 147ks
knee-high fulltoss, bottom edge, gets a single, Haddin to face the last delivery
premeditates, walks across, takes a low fulltoss and plays the pick-up shot over midwicket

inn2.comm: looks to run a length delivery to off, can't beat Ponting at point
stays full, around off, defended to cover, 142ks
back of a length, Butt opens the face of the bat, gets a single to squarish third man
low fulltoss, Kamran gets across, gets the inside part of the bat, the ball rolls along to mid-on
beaten outside off, playing for the swing and driving on the up, is beaten by the ball going along the angle
short ball, outside off, 141ks, Akmal moves outside the line - not that he is there in the first place
goes past the edge, 144ks, angling across him, tame push at the ball
misses out on a leg-side delivery, early into the shot, the ball rolls off the pad
length ball, around middle, pushed to cover
on the pads, worked away to fine leg for one
big shout for catch down the leg side, but it clips the thigh on the way - Asoka de Silva misses the connection and calls it a wide
left alone outside off
extra bounce there, beats him on the defensive shot around off, the shout for low is stifled because of the bounce
tucks him up with a short one into the ribs
just outside off, just short of length, played towards point
another short delivery, rising into the ribs, defended towards cover
punches a length ball, one bounce to Clarke at cover
looks for the pull shot, is hurried into it, and the ball limps off towards midwicket
maiden over, plays a copy-book forward defensive
peach, 150ks, and it moves away off the seam, and kicks off a length to as high as Haddin's head, Akmal has no clue, is drawn into poking at it
half-volley this time, Akmal is not in any position to hit it, pushes it back to the bowler
quick again, 147ks, pitched on a good length, headed for the off stump, defended off the back foot
and he goes past the edge again, 150ks again, leaving him, and kicking off just back of a length
punched away square, Akmal stands tall, rides the bounce, and makes good connection, with an open face
150.5ks, half-volley, though, but Butt is caught on the back foot, pushed to midwicket
and Akmal is beaten outside off again, it's kicking off a length, leaving Akmal, and Haddin has to collect it in front of his face
throws his arms at this outside off, gets a thick edge, lands safe, towards third man
edged and taken, he finally gives him the one that has to be edged, back of a length, outside off, angling in to his ribs, he has to play at it, and the healthy edge is accepted at second slip
and he has drilled the first ball he faces, right off the meat of the bat, but can't beat Clarke at cover-point
goes back to bowling short, over the stumps, Younis gets out of the line, drops his wrists

beautiful bowling, lands around middle and off, seams away, Younis is drawn into the drive, gets a healthy edge, White dives to his left, in front of the first slip, and takes the catch. Superb catch, but would have been easier for the first slip
pings him on the back foot, punched away to point
gets tall, punches another delivery square, can't get it past point
he is hitting the bat rather than the bat hitting the ball, Akmal is on the back foot again, pushing this to cover
almost another edge, Akmal's outside edge is teasing Siddle like a stripper. Good pace, just outside off, and then moving away off the seam, and he ends up playing inside the line
pushed off the back foot towards cover
driven on the up, finds neither the timing nor the placement, and Hussey makes a diving save at short mid-off
bowls length, driven on the up, nicely connected, but straight to mid-off
bounces him again, Yousuf ducks under it, called the one bouncer for the over
comes forward, and defends it to cover
wide down the leg side, the short one goes wrong
worked away off the hips, just two fielders on the leg side, gets a couple
another beauty, short delivery, just outside off, lifting from back of a length, and Yousuf has to bring out his best to get out of the way
classy off-drive, Bollinger pitches this one on a length, Yousuf leans in to it, and shows it the full face, and the check-drive flies along the outfield
lovely shot, this short delivery doesn't have the same amount of fire in it, and it's angling into Akmal, who gets under the pull shot and deposits it over square leg
Ponting makes a diving save at backward point, but misses with the direct-hit attempt, and by a long way
looks for the cut down to third man, and is beaten for the bounce
fuller this time, not driveable yet, and he defends off the front foot
shot, cut away, SIddle not quite at the same pace in this over, Yousuf gets a single to third man
back of a length, 145ks, Akmal gets behind it, and defends
starts with a length delivery, hit to wide of mid-off for one
looks for the swivel-pull, is beaten and hit in the thigh, outside the line of off
pokes at a delivery outside off, no feet, and he successfully teases another bowler with that dangling outside edge
and just like that he pulls out this big drive over the cover ring, makes good connection with an open face, and that's the length he is looking for
pulls the length back this time, played back to the bowler
back of a length again, pushed down to mid-off
good short bowling, rising towards the chest, around off, no room, defended towards cover
looks for the cut, doesn't get enough bat, but takes a single to backward point
slower ball, 128ks, offcutter, almost squeezes through, the inside edge hits the pad, and he is still not out. Umpire calls it a leg-bye, though
pushes off the back foot, towards point
fuller ball, angling in, helped away for a couple
short outside off, covers the stumps, and lets it go through to the keeper
stays back of a length, just outside off, defended off the back foot
good-looking off-drive on the up, but straight to mid-off
short delivery, over the stumps, sways out of the line
length ball, around off, drops and runs, gets a single to point
looks to steal one, but Akmal sees Ponting charging in from point, and sends Yousuf back

superb bowling followed by superb fielding from McKay! tucks Yousuf up, Akmal wants a leg-bye, but it's not gone far off, and Yousuf correctly sends him back. McKay makes a dash, turns around, and thrown the middle stump down on a half-volley. The way Akmal has been getting beaten outside off without nicking ever, run-out seemed the only way of getting him
short delivery, bounces and moves away, Umar fends at it, misses it, Haddin collects it in front of his face

two Akmals gone in three deliveries! the perfect delivery, the one that coaches tell you to bowl, "Hit the top of off"! Siddle gets it to hit the top of off, holding its line a touch, and Umar ends up playing inside the line, and reacts like Gatting did after facing Warne's first delivery of the Ashes
length delivery, shaping towards off, defended towards cover
right on the target, just outside off, angling in towards the stumps, defended towards cover
makes him fend with another short delivery, he keeps it down, though, and gets a single to third man
another bouncer, Yousuf is happy to duck
into the pads, but short, and defended towards midwicket
left alone outside off
back of a length again, just outside off, no room, all he can do is defend
goes for the bouncer, Malik sways out early, isn't that sharp anyway
length ball, Malik makes a movement half-forward, and defends
spoils a good over by angling this one too far down the leg side
shoulders arms outside off
a loosener on the pads, helped away for a couple
full delivery, driven down the ground, but straight to mid-off
length ball outside off, leaves it be
good shot, nice timing, wide of mid-off, leaning into the drive
short outside off, left alone
length ball, outside off, forward defensive
nicely worked away off the pads for a single
defended off the back foot
punched off the back foot, straight to cover-point
digs in a bouncer, Malik ducks without trouble
looks to cut, but is handcuffed by the lack of room
another short ball, and he ducks in again
short ball again, fended towards point, keeps it down
swivel-pull, too straight this short ball is, gets a single to fine leg
full ball, across him, driven to cover
short, outside off, left alone
shoulders arms again, well outside off, but not wide enough to be called
this time he bowls much straighter, making Malik play, he does well to defend it
helped away off the hips, gets a single
pushed into the covers for a single
almost played on, angling in, tucking him up, but he is safe despite the inside edge
good bouncer, head-high, right over the stumps, and Malik sways out of the line
inside edge onto the pads

Ponting pulls off a blinder at point, Malik makes room and cuts, dying on him, Ponting dives to his left, gets his left hand between the ball and the ground, smoothly done. There was no rush, no hurry, as he dived, as if he had sized that up all along, and that while diving full length
short, tucks him, defended right under his eye
another bouncer, pulled away towards midwicket
punched away off the back foot, gets a single to third man
tucks him up again with a short one
kicks at him, just outside him, Yousuf does well to keep it down, gets a single to third man
Afridi doesn't want to prod and nudge, backs away and swings, Bollinger's length is short as usual, and Afridi misses. Interesting times ahead
shoulders arms outside off
presses forward and defends a shortish delivery
fuller this time, driven, but straight to mid-on
slightly slower, length ball, defended towards point
angled too far down the leg side
inside edge onto the pad, doesn't go too far
runs this one down to third man for one
Yousuf looks to guide a back-of-a-length delivery to third man but finds backward point
Yousuf plays the loose shot, outside off, and he goes for the big drive, missing by about a foot
into the pads, worked away to fine leg
goes for the 30th row over long-on, doesn't connect, oohs and aahs all around
goes for the flick, gets a leading edge, but will take a single to mid-on
outside off, leaves it alone
And he has hit him 30 rows back here, over long-on, what a hit, jumps out of the crease, Hauritz bowls flat, and that is playing into Afridi's hands
late cut this time, smart shot, gets a single just after a six
Yousuf gets adventurous, tries the reverse-sweep, is hit in the shoulder
looks to turn it to leg, finds midwicket
throws it up wide, Yousuf comes forward and defends it with an open face
goes deep into the crease, and turns this one to fine leg for one
shoulders arms, this one nips back in, but the off stump is pretty safe
holds its line after pitching just short of a length outside off, beats the outside edge
tucks him up, gets a single to wide of midwicket

out goes Afridi, short ball, Afridi looks for a repeat of his previous hit over long-on, there is no room for him and he top-edges into the orbit, Watson tells Haddin he wants the caught-and-bowled, gets under it, and as Bob Willis would say, makes no mistake
almost another, makes him fend at another bouncer, and the edge falls inches short of a diving second slip
another bouncer, ducks out of this one without any fuss
flicked off the pads, can't beat square leg
again looks to work it to leg, can't beat short fine
stretches forward and defends
pushes forward, and works it past square leg
presses forward and defends, no spin here
there is turn and bounce here, spins past the outside edge first, and then past the off stump
Yousuf has had enough it seems, shimmies down the wicket and lofts him mover Watson, no fuss, clean as a whistle
short, tucks him up now, defended back
defends a length delivery off the front foot
looks to run it down to third man, but makes a late decision to withdraw
flicks this one off the pads, gets a single
cracking drive, Clarke at cover dives and saves four here
drift for Hauritz, defends outside off, gets turn to take the inside edge, but he is safe
turned around the corner for one
slip and silly point in place, and he bowls short and flat, and is cut away for two
goes for the slog sweep over midwicket, the big top edge clears slip
slows it down, Aamer looks to turn it to leg, gets a safe leading edge
Hauritz is becoming a caught-and-bowled specialist! this is drilled back powerfully at him, absolutely smashed, and shin high, but he gets his hands down in time, and takes it clean as a whistle
short ball, tucks him up, defended to cover
cuts this one, doesn't get any power behind it
punched off the back foot, can't get it past cover
length ball, pushes forward and defends
runs this one down to third man for one
beauty he gets first up, seams away off a length, and misses the outside edge by a coat of varnish
angling into the pads, padded away
Yousuf not farming strike, goes back and turns this around the corner for one
fired in, but still spinning in, beats him
what a catch! but by a member of the ground staff behind the long-off boundary, lovely clean hit after stepping out, and our friend here takes it off his bootlaces
inside edge past short leg and square leg and they came back for two
sweeps this one, gets a single to fine leg, retains strike
seaming in, beats the inside edge, no appeal for lbw because it is sliding down
throws the bath tub at this outside off, misses by a long way
pulls, misses, hit in the thigh
attempted yorker, and he keeps this one out, comes through for a single
short, looks to run it down to third man, but has no room
pulled away, nicely timed, over square leg, gets four more
cut away to deep point, gets a single
short, sits up to be pulled, and Yousuf obliges, gets two to wide of deep square leg
angled across him, turn in, beats him, it's the height that stifles the appeal
moves all the way across, looks for the little lap shot, but hits it straight to short fine
bat-pad, but no forward short leg in place
draws him wide and forward, Yousuf defends
full delivery, driven to sweeper-cover
connects with the paddle sweep, gets it fine of fine leg, comes back for the second
arm ball, gets an inside edge but the pad is guarding the stumps
tossed up, driven back to the bowler
goes for the big shot, mis-hits, but gets a single down to long-on
pushed away to the left of Clarke, who does well to field
short, pulled straight towards deep square
comes down the wicket, and drives powerfully, gets a single to long-off
topspinner, just outside off, goes back and across and defends
swept away for a single
presses forward and drives to wide of long-off, gets a couple
jumps out of the tracks and pads it away, and it has gone back to Hauritz on the full, and they haven't even appealed, it has gone off the pad onto the glove, and there's a wicket gone a-begging
full ball, driven down the ground and he takes a single
driven past cover for one
premeditates a paddle sweep, connects it
pushed down the ground for a single
defended off the front foot towards cover
50 for Yosuf, cuts this straighter delivery past point and comes back for two
pushes this one down to long-on
another six for Rana, steps out, gets to the pitch of it, and goes over midwicket, the longer boundary
cut away for four this time, expecting the shorter delivery, and crashes it away past point
looks for the paddle sweep, can't get it past short fine

and he's a goner, superb stumping by Haddin, tosses this up, teasing him, and Rana is beaten in the flight, the ball turns sharply down the leg side and Haddin is super-quick, although off balance because of the sharp turn
lovely chip shot, steps down, gets to the pitch of it, and lofts him  over midwicket
turn there, cuts it, but not past point
inside-out, but can't go over extra, instead, chips it one-bounce to long-off
tossed up outside off, shoulders arms
flatter, on the stumps, defended
just outside off, gets onto the front foot and defends it to cover
starts off with a length ball, defended back to the bowler
goes for the slog, it's bowled wide of off, and beats the edge
beats him outside off again, Yousuf looks to run it down to third man but is beaten by the angle
this time he connects with that dab shot and gets a single
full delivery, Gul gets the bat down in time and defends
the first forceful shot tried by Gul, is beaten outside off
angling into the pads, Yousuf misses on the pick-up shot

six feet either side and it would be four! Moves across the stumps, flicks, nicely connected but straight to Hauritz at short fine. Mark Nicholas sumps it up on Channel 9: "I guess if it isn't your day, it isn't your night either."
and gets a nice bouncer first up, moves out of the line just in time
pitched up outside off, slashes and misses
looks to run it to third man - despite a slip in place - and he misses
throws his bat at a wide delivery, gets it over point for one
bouncer to No. 11, No Country For Nice Men, and he ducks under it
goes for the bog drive and misses by a long way
beaten outside off again, good bounce there
looks to run it down again, but deliberately plays it inside the line
stays inside the line again
full delivery, and this is pushed down the ground off the middle of the bat
Gul pulls, and misses by a long distance
tucks him up, worked away to fine leg for one
it's all over, Ajmal pokes outside off and the outside edge settles in Haddin's gloves to finish this mauling at the SCG
